results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of connected labeled graphs with n edges and k vertices, 1 <= k <= n+1.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1325 (rows 0..50)
program: Row(n)={Vec(serlaplace(polcoef(log(O(x^2*x^n)+sum(k=0, n+1, x^k*(1 + y + O(y*y^n))^binomial(k, 2)/k!)), n, y)), -(n+1))}
xref: Subsequent diagonals give the number of connected labeled graphs with n nodes and n+k edges for k=0..11: A057500, A061540, A061541, A061542, A061543, A096117, A061544 A096150, A096224, A182294, A182295, A182371.
Cf. A054923 (unlabeled), A062734 (transpose), A290776 (multigraphs), A322147 (loops allowed), A331437 (series-reduced).
